Equity Bank, the country's largest lender by deposit accounts, won the Resilience Impact Award during the annual international Global Resilience Summit also known as RESCON.The lender was recognised for its work in creating resilience through capacity building, improving livelihoods, innovations in cash transfers for recipients in remote and harsh terrain areas.Equity was also lauded for work in refugee camps in Kenya and Rwanda, including Kakuma and Dadaab camps and for its leadership role as chair of the East Africa Humanitarian Private Sector Partnership Platform. &ldquo;Through our financial intermediation and social impact investments Equity Bank will continue to support its people in their social economic transformational journey,&rdquo; Equity Bank director for special projects Allan Waititu said in a statement.